criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  60 years of age or older;

          -  relative body fat ≥ 32 assessed by whole body dual-energy X-ray absorptiometry (DXA);

          -  physically independent;

          -  free from cardiac or orthopedic dysfunction that would have precluded them from
             performing the tests or the training program associated with the study;

          -  not receiving hormonal replacement therapy;

          -  not performing physical exercise more than once a week in the six months preceding the
             beginning of the investigation.

        Exclusion Criteria:

        • All subjects not participating in 85% of the total sessions of training or withdrawl
